    "turn-86-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Good. So we're seeing that the issue of the e's and o's splitting is about stress. When we don't stress them, they stay intact.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-86-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "09fb758d23a2784a32ba48fb26067d48ce7cbaa9caedcb695bfd21c32116457a"
        }
      ]
    },
    "outro-1-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "You've learned how stress affects verb stem changes in Spanish, focusing on e to ie and o to ue transformations.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "outro-1-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "4a489afe038e36057417143cf07a0680804b88a65321d4a25d88da4348d0ee4b"
        }
      ]
    },
    "outro-2-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Try conjugating other verbs you know and see if they follow the same pattern. Practice with verbs like 'entender' or 'volver'.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "outro-2-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "f4fc0ce1bca871d4b987e8335b94e245a49e22e64b345d222d3efbd77a3ebf21"
        }
      ]
    },
    "outro-3-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Understanding these patterns will help you predict and use verb forms more accurately in conversation.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "outro-3-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "921c9ecafa925ef40e2e93986e904674bb71bb0e1a9eaed90a924807d96a8233"
        }
